3 Sec. C-8. Transition provisions; Community Resilience Partnership
4 Program. The following provisions govern the transition of the administration of the
5 Community Resilience Partnership Program, established in the Maine Revised Statutes,
6 Title 5, section 3109, from the Office of Policy Innovation and the Future to the Maine
7 Office of Community Affairs, State Resilience Office.
8 1. All existing rules, regulations and procedures in effect, in operation or adopted for
9 the Community Resilience Partnership Program in the Office of Policy Innovation and the
10 Future or any of its administrative units or officers are hereby declared in effect and
11 continue in effect until rescinded, revised or amended by the Maine Office of Community
12 Affairs, State Resilience Office.
13 2. All existing contracts, agreements and compacts currently in effect in the
14 Community Resilience Partnership Program continue in effect.
15 3. All records, property and equipment previously belonging to or allocated for the use
16 of the Community Resilience Partnership Program in the Office of Policy Innovation and
17 the Future become, on the effective date of this Act, part of the property of the Maine Office
18 of Community Affairs, State Resilience Office.
19 4. All existing forms, licenses, letterheads and similar items bearing the name of or
20 referring to the Community Resilience Partnership Program may be used by the Maine
21 Office of Community Affairs, State Resilience Office until existing supplies of those items
22 are exhausted.
23 5. Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, the State Controller shall
24 transfer any unobligated balances remaining in the Community Resilience Partnership
25 Program Other Special Revenue Funds account and federal funds to the Maine Office of
26 Community Affairs, State Resilience Office no later than October 1, 2025.
