3215 Sec. C-10. Contingent effective date; continuation of obligations. Those
3226 sections of this Part that amend the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 3109,
3237 subsection 2 and Title 12, sections 408 and 409 and that portion of this Part that enacts
3248 Title 5, section 3211, subsection 2 are contingent on the State Resilience Office established
3259 in Title 5, section 3211 receiving funds sufficient to administer the floodplain management
3360 program established in Title 12, section 408, the State Floodplain Mapping Fund
3371 established in Title 12, section 409 and the Community Resilience Partnership Program
3382 established in Title 5, section 3109. Until that contingency is met, the Department of
3393 Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry shall continue to administer the floodplain
4304 management program and the State Floodplain Mapping Fund and the Office of Policy
4315 Innovation and the Future shall continue to administer the Community Resilience
4326 Partnership Program. The Director of the Maine Office of Community Affairs shall notify
4337 the Secretary of State, the Secretary of the Senate, the Clerk of the House of
4348 Representatives and the Revisor of Statutes when the State Resilience Office receives funds
4359 sufficient to administer the programs under this section.'
